This canteen is made of shaped and hardened leather and plugged with a cloth bound wooden stopper. A short length of thin frayed rope allows it to be easily slung about your shoulder, neck, or belt. 

Target yourself to drink form the canteen
Target the canteen to empty it.
Target the ground  or a placeable object  to fill the canteen from that source.
A standard disposable torch. It   had only a limited amount of burn life. Carry several if you plan to be in the dark for a while.

A bundle of firewood for making or fueling a campfire.

Target the ground to build a campfire, or target a campfire to extend the life of that campfire.
Compact, dry norishing foods suitable for travel. They come pre-wrapped in a handy cloth container.
This bottle of wine is good for about 6 servings when full.
This hefty stein of beer holds four pints.
A cut of cooked, dried and extremely salted ham. Makes a good meal and travels well too.
